	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />&quot;Bolero&quot; is modern orchestral music, not classical music. <em>The Legend of Zelda</em> was going to have &quot;Bolero&quot; at some point in the game until <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20121014080606/http://www.1up.com/features/zelda-exposed?pager.offset=7" class="postlink">Maurice Ravel's publisher complained</a>. Copyright in Ravel's works expired in most of the world at the end of 2007, but U.S. copyright in &quot;Bolero&quot; doesn't expire until 2024.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


